    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-26T06:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-26T06:35:00-05:00" n="266"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d266">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.01A/176: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-26T15:00:00+03:25"
                            >June 26, 1942—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 26—11:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>316. Reference my telegram 191, June 9 and despatch 279, June 11.<note n="17"
                        xml:id="d266fn17">Latter not printed.</note> Prime Minister called me today
                    to express his deep concern over <pb facs="0254" n="242" xml:id="pg_242"/>
                    failure of American Government to respond to his many requests for advisers,
                    particularly Food Administrator and financial mission. He said he had promised
                    the Majlis on occasion of expulsion of Japanese Legation<note n="18"
                        xml:id="d266fn18">For correspondence on this subject, see <ref
                            target="#pg_325">pp. 325</ref> ff.</note> and when other action
                    favorable to Allies was taken that effective aid from United States would soon
                    be forthcoming. He added in evident agitation that he is “getting near the end
                    of his rope” and that his position may soon become untenable unless American
                    help is extended.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
